MathApp allows users to select a mathematical operation, the mobile device will send the operation to BeanStalk where the server
will return a math equation back to the mobile application. The user will then answer the equation and send the answer back to the
server to be vaidated. If the answer is correct the server will send a 0 back to the mobile device to luanch the correct fragment.
If the answer is incorrect the server will send a 1 back to the mobile device to launch the incorrect fragment. 
Upon clicking the "I know" button on the correct fragment the application will reset itself.
Upon clicking the "Try again" button on the incorrect fragment the application will pop the fragment off the backstack and allow
the user to try again.
